    <edge source="NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM" target="EMERGENCY DEPARTMENTS">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">EMERGENCY DEPARTMENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Negative-pressurized isolation rooms are implemented in Emergency Departments to contain infectious patients and prevent contaminated air from migrating to ED corridors; effectiveness depends on maintained pressure differential and proper exhaust configuration. (Validated in Wang et al. 2022.)</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM" target="HOSPITAL ISOLATION ROOM">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">HOSPITAL ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">A negative-pressurized isolation room is a specific engineering-control instantiation used within hospital isolation rooms to provide containment via inward airflow and dedicated exhaust.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM" target="RESPIRATORY VIRUSES">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">Designed to limit dissemination of respiratory viruses by containing and exhausting virus-laden aerosols from the patient environment.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">When used for patients with SARS-CoV-2 infection, the negative-pressure containment strategy specifically targets reduction of Covid-19 aerosol dissemination from the patient room.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM" target="COUGH-GENERATED DROPLET/AEROSOL BEHAVIOR AND AIRBORNE PERSISTENCE">
      <data key="d7">NEGATIVE-PRESSURIZED ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED DROPLET/AEROSOL BEHAVIOR AND AIRBORNE PERSISTENCE</data>
      <data key="d9">REDUCES</data>
      <data key="d10">By maintaining inward airflow and directing room air to exhaust, negative-pressure rooms can reduce airborne persistence and alter transport pathways of cough-generated droplets/aerosols, lowering exposure in adjacent zones (effectiveness depends on room design and ventilation rates).</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION" target="HOSPITAL ISOLATION ROOM">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">HOSPITAL ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation systems and configuration choices (supply/exhaust placement, flow rates) are applied within hospital isolation rooms to control airborne contaminant concentration and transport.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION" target="EMERGENCY DEPARTMENTS">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">EMERGENCY DEPARTMENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation strategies are implemented in Emergency Department spaces, including ED isolation rooms, with configuration and operational constraints unique to ED environments.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation aims to reduce airborne exposure to SARS-CoV-2 by dilution, directed airflow, and removal of virus-laden aerosols from occupied zones.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION" target="RESPIRATORY VIRUSES">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">RESPIRATORY VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">More generally, ventilation is used to mitigate transmission risk from respiratory viruses by reducing aerosol concentrations and modifying transport pathways.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
