      <data key="d7">VENTILATION</data>
      <data key="d8">COUGH-GENERATED DROPLET/AEROSOL BEHAVIOR AND AIRBORNE PERSISTENCE</data>
      <data key="d9">REDUCES</data>
      <data key="d10">Different ventilation configurations can reduce airborne persistence of cough-generated droplets/aerosols and change trajectories to decrease exposure in key breathing zones; demonstrated experimentally/computationally in Dao et al. (2022).</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
